message.content: cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.MM (Computer Vision, Medical Imaging, Information Theory, Machine Learning, Multimedia) - The paper deals with medical image compression, specifically mammograms, using a fully convolutional autoencoder and arithmetic coding. This involves techniques from computer vision (convolutional neural networks), medical imaging (mammograms), information theory (arithmetic coding), machine learning (autoencoders), and multimedia (image compression). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.MM and cs.IT. cs.LG and cs.MM are also possible due to the use of deep learning and multimedia techniques.
